{
  "texts": [
    "SWaT Water Treatment Testbed and datasetsThe SWaT water treatment (see Fig. 4) is a six-stage process (P 1 to P 6) and emulates a typical treatment plant.",
    "The water for treatment is the input to P 1 and treated water is the main output of P 6.",
    "Different (and redundant) sensors are strategically placed to make measurements across the testbed.",
    "Actuators are used for control.",
    "The sensors and actuators used in P 1 -P 6 appear in TABLE 1."
  ]
}